We use Confluence onDemand.

When adding an issue macro to a wiki page marking a single issue, the page is then marked as mentioning the issue in the issue links section in JIRA. This is very useful integration.

However, when the macro is added to the comment section, the same link is not created. So if the commenter wants his link to appear in JIRA has only 2 choices, both of them requiring additional manual operations:
* add a Confluence reference from within the JIRA issue as a link;
* have the issue macro added to the main wiki page.

It would be nice to be able to configure globally for the site, and perhaps also for each space, the behavior and allow or not allow issue macros containing a single issue to automatically link the confluence page to the issue just like it happens when the issue macro is added to the wiki page content itself.

